  "body": "## summary\r\n\r\nforge outputs JSON ABIs like the following:\r\n\r\n```json\r\n{\r\n  \"type\": \"function\",\r\n  \"name\": \"blockHeightToHash\",\r\n  \"inputs\":[{\"internalType\":\"uint256\",\"name\":\"\",\"type\":\"uint256\"}],\r\n  \"outputs\":[{\"internalType\":\"bytes32\",\"name\":\"\",\"type\":\"bytes32\"}],\r\n  \"constant\": false,\r\n  \"stateMutability\": \"pure\"\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhen loading in ethers.js, this gives the following (slightly misleading) error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nError: cannot have constant function with mutability view (argument=\"value\", value={\"type\":\"function\",\"name\":\"blockHeightToHash\",\"inputs\":[{\"internalType\":\"uint256\",\"name\":\"\",\"type\":\"uint256\"}],\"outputs\":[{\"internalType\":\"bytes32\",\"name\":\"\",\"type\":\"bytes32\"}],\"constant\":false,\"stateMutability\":\"view\"}, code=INVALID_ARGUMENT, version=abi/5.5.0)\r\n```\r\n\r\nlooking deeper, it appears that ethers.js expects `\"constant\"` to be true if and only if `\"stateMutability\"` is `\"view\"` or `\"pure\"`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/73a46efea32c3f9a4833ed77896a216e3d3752a0/packages/abi/src.ts/fragments.ts#L661-L663\r\n\r\n\r\n### version\r\n\r\n```\r\nfoundry-cli 0.1.0\r\nethers 5.5.3\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n",
